# Internationalization (Czech UI)

## User-facing text
- All strings visible to users must be in **Czech** (labels, buttons, errors, emails, toasts, empty states).
- Do not add hardcoded English UI strings; use Czech equivalents consistent with existing copy in the repo.

## Exceptions (English allowed)
- Code identifiers, env var names, API field names, log prefixes, and third-party SDK constants.
- Proper nouns and brand names (e.g. Withings, Stripe, Spoonacular) where already established.

## Review checklist
- New UI component: scan for quoted English phrases before finishing.
- API error messages returned to the client: Czech, actionable, no stack traces.
